Complex sentences:
- Sentences 2-3: Sentences 2-3 contain one clause each but 2-3 combined contains two which would make it a complex sentence in some applications. Though following the most precise rules, we will not class this example as complex.
- Sentence 4: Two clauses separated by "som en utvärdering av FEM programmet... "  making this complex.

Average number of words per sentence: 
- Sentence 1: 20 words
- Sentence 2: 12 words 
- Sentence 3: 8 words
 Average: (20+12+8)/3 = 40/3 = 13.33 words per sentence

The percentage of long words is (7 long words / 52 total words) * 100 ≈ 13.46
The percentage of complex sentences is (1 complex sentence / 3 total sentences) * 100 = 33.33
Average number of words per sentence: 13.33

LIX = (13.46) + (33.33) + (13.33) ≈ 60.12